"""Give me code to create an example python pandas dataframe. The dataframe should have 3 columns: "Name", "Age", "Lucky Number". Create 10 rows of data. The lucky number should be between 1 and 1000000. Use the pandas and numpy libraries to do this" ** See that I am explicit in what I want to create. I specify the names and numbers of rows and columns. I also specify the libraries used. I use common libraries like Pandas, Numpy.If you are new to a language, process, etc. you might not know the specifics to use. """import pandas as pdimport numpy as np# Set seed for reproducibilitynp.random.seed(42)# Generate datanames = [f"Person_{i}" for i in range(1, 11)]ages = np.random.randint(18, 65, size=10)lucky_numbers = np.random.randint(1, 1000001, size=10)# Create DataFramedf = pd.DataFrame({    "Name": names,    "Age": ages,    "Lucky Number": lucky_numbers})# Display the DataFrameprint(df)"""**Give Examples in your prompt! Tell the AI explicitly what you want it to doI want the names to look like this: John, Bob, Mary, Sally instead of Person_1, Person_2"""import pandas as pdimport numpy as np# Define a list of namesnames = ["John", "Bob", "Mary", "Sally", "Alice", "Tom", "Linda", "James", "Karen", "Steve"]# Generate random ages and lucky numbersages = np.random.randint(18, 65, size=10)lucky_numbers = np.random.randint(1, 1000001, size=10)# Create the DataFramedf = pd.DataFrame({    "Name": names,    "Age": ages,    "Lucky Number": lucky_numbers})# Display the DataFrameprint(df)